{"word":"ἀμφιθαλής","slug":"ἀμφιθαλής","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀμφιθαλής</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:θάλλω'><el>θάλλω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>blooming on both sides</i>, of children who have both parents alive, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>all abounding</i>, of the gods, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>:—<a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>abounding in</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}